cs351.project2

Class OrderedGenomeList

  • java.lang.Object
    • cs351.project2.OrderedGenomeList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Tribe, java.lang.Iterable<Genome>

    public final class OrderedGenomeList
extends java.lang.Object
implements Tribe, java.lang.Iterable<Genome>
    An OrderedGenomeList provides an easy way for storing Genomes and for maintaining their order. If external sources modify the Genome fitness values, sort() can be called manually. Otherwise, sort() will be called internally whenever it is critical that the list be resorted (such as when returning an iterator for the list after things had been added).
